<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">-&gt; </span><span style="color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">npm </span><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #ffcc99;">install</span></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="color: #000000;"> to install</span> package graph-ts already defined in our package.json file</span></p>"}],["code",{"code":"type AddressValue @entity {
  id: ID!
  count: Int!
}
type Address @entity {
  id: ID!
  timesChange: Int!
  blockNumber: BigInt!
  timestamp: BigInt!
  currentValue: BigInt!
}","language":"graphql"}],["code",{"code":"    source:
      address: "0x261eceB52b36D931f3Ec3742a6b66Deb720d8Fe4"
      abi: RandomAssignment
      startBlock: 10263362","language":"graphql"}],["code",{"code":"entities:
        - AddressValue
        - Address","language":"graphql"}],["code",{"code":"   eventHandlers:
        - event: Assign(indexed address,indexed uint256)
          handler: handleAssign","language":"graphql"}],["html",{"html":"<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">-&gt; </span><span style="font-weight: 400; background-color: #000000; color: #ffff99;">graph codegen</span></p>"}],["code",{"code":"import { Assign as AssignEvent } from "../generated/RandomAssignment/RandomAssignment"
import { AddressValue, Address } from "../generated/schema";","language":"graphql"}],["code",{"code":"export function handleAssign(event: AssignEvent): void {
  let val = AddressValue.load(event.params.value.toString());
  if(!val){
    val = new AddressValue(event.params.value.toString());
    val.count = 0;
  }
  let address = Address.load(event.params.addr.toHexString());
  if(!address){
    val.count++;
    address = new Address(event.params.addr.toHexString());
    address.timesChange = 0;
  }
  address.blockNumber = event.block.number;
  address.timesChange++;
  address.timestamp = event.block.timestamp;
  address.currentValue = event.params.value;
  address.save();
  val.save();
}","language":"graphql"}]],"markups":[["em"],["strong"],["a",["href","https://thegraph.com/studio/"]]],"sections":[[1,"p",[[0,[0],1,"Subgraphs are data-querying APIs in the Graph ecosystem. A subgraph includes various types of information such as the data source, which blocks for indexing, which events to notice, how the data will be retrieved, or schema that data should be stored. Indexing nodes only need to follow instructions in subgraphs to function."]]],[1,"h2",[[0,[1],1,"Setup contract"]]],[10,0],[10,1],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Now in our DApp, we want to get a set of addresses that are assigned value more than 2 times in this smart contract. More complicated, we want to get a set of addresses assigned with current value from 5 to 10 counting from the second address from block "],[0,[0],1,"10228285"],[0,[],0," forward sorted in ascending order of value. We also want to get data on how many addresses each value is assigned."]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"We can do it by Web3 normally, but here we will use The Graph Protocol to create open APIs allowing us to query all information much easier and faster in real-time."]]],[10,2],[1,"h2",[[0,[1],1,"Create decentralized subgraph by Subgraph Studio"]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"First, go to "],[0,[2],1,"My Subgraphs | Subgraph Studio (thegraph.com)"],[0,[],0,"  Connect your wallet -> Sign message to Log in to Studio -> Create Subgraph:"]]],[10,3],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"-> Set subgraph’s name -> Hit “Continue”"]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Here if you don’t have NodeJS installed, you need to install it first."]]],[10,4],[10,5],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"-> Then we set some information such as network Rinkeby, contract address specific above,..."]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Note that if you haven’t published your code on Etherscan, you must provide the ABI file. Here I copy ABI when compiling the contract on Remix and paste it to the file abi.json"]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"The graph-cli will create a sample subgraph project for your contract. To create a subgraph, you need to modify 3 files: subgraph.yaml, schema.graphql and src/mapping.ts"]]],[10,6],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"We need this library to the write Typescript file"]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"-> In the file schema.graphql, we define each entity(schema) of data that we want to get in our DApp:"]]],[10,7],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"We need to define 2 entities: Address and AddressValue. We want to get how many addresses each value is assigned, so it is the field “count” in “AddressValue”. In “Address”, we want to count how many times the address has been assigned a value(timeChanged), currentValue, blockNumber, and timestamp. The field “id” with the type “ID!” is unique and required in every entity."]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"-> In file subgraph.yaml, we write configuration for the subgraph like the entities, startBlock, event to catch:"]]],[10,8],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Here we define the startBlock as the number of the block that the data source starts indexing from. In most cases, we suggest using the block in which the contract was created, if not then the indexer will start from the genesis block."]]],[10,9],[1,"p",[[1,[],0,0],[0,[],0,"These two entities are those we defined in the file schema.graphql before"]]],[10,10],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"It means when the event “Assign” is emitted from the smart contract, it will update data by calling the function “handleAssign” that we will define in mapping.ts"]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Numerous contracts avoid emitting events so that gas costs can be reduced. In these instances, events are not an effective way to collect relevant changes to the state of a contract. The Graph also uses "],[0,[0],1,"callHandler"],[0,[],0," and "],[0,[0],1,"blockHandler"],[0,[],0," to catch new blocks and all function calls or interact with IPFS. "]]],[10,11],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"To make smart contracts, events, and entities easy and type-safe, the Graph CLI generates AssemblyScript types from a combination of the subgraph's GraphQL schema and the contract ABIs included in the data sources. This command creates a new folder generated containing AssemblyScript."]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"-> The main part is the mapping.ts file which we determine how the data is obtained from the blockchain:"]]],[10,12],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"We need to import all entities defined in schema.graphql to get data for them in this file. The Graph will run from the startBlock to the newest block, catch all events chronologically and handle it via the corresponding handler function in mapping.ts"]]],[10,13],[1,"p",[]]],"ghostVersion":"4.0"}

