4. Deploy to network

To deploy the smart contract to the Ethereum network, we execute the below
command

$ truffle migrate --network rinkeby

If everything goes right, you’ll get a contract address like this

0xa58e2E3492d160EC200306E98a8C455709953dBe

Check out the Rinkeby network’s explorer to ensure your contract is created
successfully. In my case, accessing this link
[https://rinkeby.etherscan.io/address/0xa58e2E3492d160EC200306E98a8C455709953dBe] 
will show information like this:

5. Test

Select Import Tokens from MetaMask Extension on Chrome and paste your contract
address into the Token Contract Address’s input field. Then, click Add Custom
Token to import your ERC-20 token.

Your token has been added to the wallet; it will be available under the assets
section in Metamask.

My wallet owns 100 AUG because my smart contract has a constructor that
initializes my address's balance to equal the total supply of my token.

Conclusion
The ERC-20 is a standard for Fungible Tokens. With this standard, you can deploy
your own token, which can be exchanged with others. In addition to the ERC-20
standard, there are many other types of tokens standard like ERC-721,
ERC-1155,... Subscribe to our TechFi for more articles and guilds on Ethereum.

